originalText.text: Horrible place to park your nice car payed $45 for over night parking drove from Boston to NY to see my uncle figured my car would be much safer here vs parking in the street and came back to find these scratches on my car talked to the manager and said he couldn't see anything on the cameras and wouldn't help out in any way no refund or free parking next time for the poor service his name is Guillermo definitely won't be parking my car here either I hope everyone see this review might save you the headache

originalText.text:
Unprofessional and shady.

Good people working the garage. Can't say the same for the management.

I have been a customer of this garage for the last 3 months. Called the management office to ask about a sudden rate change - was told two different rates from two different people. Ultimately decided to cancel my parking spot, which they responded to aggressively: "if you don't tell us the garage you're changing to, we're charging you more for this month". Absurd and unprofessional. Don't get caught up with these guys, not worth the hassle.

originalText.text: DO NOT USE THIS GARAGE! I drive a classic car strictly for leisure purposes. I have never street parked it. I used this garage for monthly parking.  The day I brought my car here it was mint. One month later my car is cover in dents and scratches. I have personally watched them crash cars into other cars and back cars into walls. The management will not respond to any emails or phone calls. BEWARE!
